channel.title: How do I port forward (Without LINKSYS!)
channel.description: My router doesnt have that. It has some other thing. But its not that. Most guides I see only explain the way to Port Forward with LINKSYS. I know there are other ways to Port Forward.. If you can step me through Port Forwarding without LINKSYS I would greatly appreciate it!

item.description:
@silly_faggit wrote:

Ok I looked at my router… It is LINKSYS…

Problem is… If i type in 192.168.1.102 (my computer specifically) Onto the adress bar. It will come to ‘page not found’.

How do I know what the IP the the router is?

If I type in 192.168.1.1 Like the defualt is supposed to be for routers (I think!) Then it comes up to a thing that looks like LINKSYS, But it is called NETWORK EVERYWHERE. And at the top it says Cable/DSL basic router setup.

I dont have NETWORK EVERYWHERE for a router though. I got LINKSYS!!!

Can someone please help me!
